Title: Race to Witch Mountain
Description: A Las Vegas cabbie enlists the help of a UFO expert to protect two siblings with paranormal powers from the clutches of an organization that wants to use the kids for their nefarious plans.

Title: The Sisterhood of the Travelling Pants
Description: Four best girlfriends hatch a plan to stay connected with one another as their lives start off in different directions: they pass around a pair of secondhand jeans that fits each of their bodies perfectly.

Title: House on Haunted Hill
Description: An amusement park mogul offers a group of diverse people $1,000,000 to spend the night in a haunted house with a horrifying past.

Title: The Death of Stalin
Description: Moscow, 1953. After being in power for nearly 30 years, Soviet dictator Josef Stalin takes ill and quickly dies. Now the members of the Council of Ministers scramble for power.

Title: The Legend of Hercules
Description: The origin story of the mythical Greek hero. Betrayed by his stepfather, the King, and exiled and sold into slavery because of a forbidden love, Hercules must use his formidable powers to fight his way back to his rightful kingdom.

Title: Original Sin
Description: A woman, along with her lover, plans to con a rich man by marrying him, earning his trust, and then running away with all his money. Everything goes as planned until she falls in love with him.

Title: The Boxtrolls
Description: A young orphaned boy raised by underground cave-dwelling trash collectors tries to save his friends from an evil exterminator.

Title: Wicker Park
Description: A young Chicago advertising executive believes a woman he sees in a café is his long-lost love. His belief leads to obsession, as he puts his life on hold in order to trail her.

Title: Friday the 13th Part 2
Description: Mrs. Voorhees is dead, and Camp Crystal Lake is shut down, but a camp next to the infamous place is stalked by an unknown assailant.

Title: Criminal
Description: In a last-ditch effort to stop a diabolical plot, a dead CIA operative's memories, secrets, and skills are implanted into a death-row inmate in hopes that he will complete the operative's mission.

Title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars
Description: After the Republic's victory on Christophsis, Anakin and his new apprentice Ahsoka Tano must rescue the kidnapped son of Jabba the Hutt. Political intrigue complicates their mission.

Title: Away We Go
Description: A couple who is expecting their first child travel around the U.S. in order to find a perfect place to start their family. Along the way, they have misadventures and find fresh connections with an assortment of relatives and old friends who just might help them discover "home" on their own terms for the first time.

Title: Lake Placid
Description: Three people attempt to stop a gigantic crocodile, who is terrorizing residents in Black Lake, Maine.

Title: Flight of the Phoenix
Description: Survivors of a plane crash in the Mongolian desert work together to build a new plane.

Title: Crocodile Dundee II
Description: Australian outback expert protects his New York love from gangsters who've followed her down under.

Title: Stealth
Description: Deeply ensconced in a top-secret military program, three pilots struggle to bring an artificial intelligence program under control before it initiates the next world war.

Title: Keeping Up with the Joneses
Description: A suburban couple becomes embroiled in an international espionage plot when they discover that their seemingly perfect new neighbors are government spies.

Title: The Majestic
Description: Set in 1951, a blacklisted Hollywood writer gets into a car accident, loses his memory and settles down in a small town where he is mistaken for a long-lost son.

Title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
Description: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

Title: Sexy Beast
Description: Brutal gangster Don Logan recruits "retired" safecracker Gal for one last job, but it goes badly for both of them.

Title: Cheaper by the Dozen 2
Description: The Bakers, while on vacation, find themselves competing with a rival family of eight children.

Title: Session 9
Description: Tensions rise within an asbestos cleaning crew as they work in an abandoned mental hospital with a horrific past that seems to be coming back.

Title: How High
Description: Two guys by the name of Silas and Jamal decided to one day smoke something magical, which eventually helps them to ace their college entrance exam.

Title: Queen of the Damned
Description: The vampire Lestat becomes a rock star whose music wakes up the queen of all vampires.

Title: Young Guns
Description: A group of young gunmen, led by Billy the Kid, become deputies to avenge the murder of the rancher who became their benefactor. But when Billy takes their authority too far, they become the hunted.

Title: Casanova
Description: The fabled romantic Giacomo Casanova, after failing to win the affection of the Venetian woman Francesca Bruni, strives to discover the real meaning of love.

Title: My Blueberry Nights
Description: A young lonely woman takes a soul-searching journey across America to resolve her questions about love while encountering a series of offbeat characters along the way.

Title: Murder by Numbers
Description: Two gifted high school students execute a "perfect" murder - then become engaged in an intellectual contest with a seasoned homicide detective.

Title: Chaplin
Description: A film about the troubled and controversial life of the master comedy filmmaker Charles Chaplin.

Title: The Pledge
Description: A retiring police chief pledges to catch the killer of a young child.

Title: Eight Legged Freaks
Description: Venomous spiders get exposed to a noxious chemical that causes them to grow to monumental proportions.

Title: Wet Hot American Summer
Description: Set on the last day of camp, in the hot summer of 1981, a group of counselors try to complete their unfinished business before the day ends.

Title: Quills
Description: In a Napoleonic era insane asylum, an inmate, the irrepressible Marquis De Sade, fights a battle of wills against a tyrannically prudish doctor.

Title: The Dark Crystal
Description: On another planet in the distant past, a Gelfling embarks on a quest to find the missing shard of a magical crystal, and so restore order to his world.

Title: Lords of Dogtown
Description: The film follows the surf and skateboarding trends that originated in Venice, California during the 1970's.

Title: Gnomeo & Juliet
Description: The neighboring gardens of Montague and Capulet are at war, but the gnomes, Gnomeo and Juliet, are in love.

Title: Arthur
Description: A drunken playboy stands to lose a wealthy inheritance when he falls for a woman his family doesn't like.

Title: All Good Things
Description: Mr. David Marks was suspected but never tried for killing his wife Katie who disappeared in 1982, but the truth is eventually revealed.

Title: Copycat
Description: An agoraphobic psychologist and a female detective must work together to take down a serial killer who copies serial killers from the past.

Title: Inland Empire
Description: As an actress starts to adopt the persona of her character in a film, her world starts to become nightmarish and surreal.

Title: Tristan + Isolde
Description: An affair between the second in line to Britain's throne and the princess of the feuding Irish spells doom for the young lovers.

Title: Innerspace
Description: A hapless store clerk must foil criminals to save the life of the man who, miniaturized in a secret experiment, was accidentally injected into him.

Title: Night on Earth
Description: An anthology of 5 different cab drivers in 5 American and European cities and their remarkable fares on the same eventful night.

Title: The World's Fastest Indian
Description: The story of New Zealander Burt Munro, who spent years rebuilding a 1920 Indian motorcycle, which helped him set the land speed world record at Utah's Bonneville Salt Flats in 1967.

Title: Stuck on You
Description: Conjoined twins from Martha's Vineyard move to Los Angeles so that one of them can pursue an acting career.

Title: The Eye
Description: A woman receives an eye transplant that allows her to see into the supernatural world.

Title: The Gods Must Be Crazy
Description: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.

Title: Vampire Academy
Description: Rose Hathaway is a Dhampir, half human-half vampire, a guardian of the Moroi, peaceful, mortal vampires living discreetly within our world. Her calling is to protect the Moroi from bloodthirsty, immortal Vampires, the Strigoi.

Title: A Dog's Purpose
Description: A dog looks to discover his purpose in life over the course of several lifetimes and owners.

Title: Irrational Man
Description: A tormented philosophy professor finds a will to live when he commits an existential act.

Title: The Player
Description: A Hollywood studio executive is being sent death threats by a writer whose script he rejected, but which one?

Title: Heartbreakers
Description: A mother and daughter con team seduce and scam wealthy men.

Title: A New York Winter's Tale
Description: A burglar falls for an heiress as she dies in his arms. When he learns that he has the gift of reincarnation, he sets out to save her.

Title: The Condemned
Description: Jack Conrad is awaiting the death penalty in a corrupt Central American prison. He is "purchased" by a wealthy television producer and taken to a desolate island where he must fight to the death against nine other condemned killers from all corners of the world, with freedom going to the sole survivor.

Title: The Jerk
Description: An idiotic man struggles to make it through life on his own in St. Louis.

Title: Storks
Description: Storks have moved on from delivering babies to packages. But when an order for a baby appears, the best delivery stork must scramble to fix the error by delivering the baby.

Title: The Soloist
Description: A newspaper journalist discovers a homeless musical genius and tries to improve his situation.

Title: Hesher
Description: A young boy has lost his mother and is losing touch with his father and the world around him. Then he meets Hesher who manages to make his life even more chaotic.

Title: The General's Daughter
Description: When the daughter of a well-known and well-respected base commander is murdered, an undercover detective is summoned to look into the matter and finds a slew of cover-ups at West Point.

Title: Terms of Endearment
Description: Follows hard-to-please Aurora looking for love, and her daughter's family problems.

Title: Vampires
Description: Recovering from an ambush that killed his entire team, a vengeful vampire slayer must retrieve an ancient Catholic relic that, should it be acquired by vampires, will allow them to walk in sunlight.

Title: Chariots of Fire
Description: Two British track athletes, one a determined Jew, and the other a devout Christian, compete in the 1924 Olympics.

Title: After Hours
Description: An ordinary word processor has the worst night of his life after he agrees to visit a girl in Soho who he met that evening at a coffee shop.

Title: Hudson Hawk
Description: A cat burglar is forced to steal Da Vinci works of art for a world domination plot.

Title: A River Runs Through It
Description: The story about two sons of a stern minister -- one reserved, one rebellious -- growing up in rural Montana while devoted to fly fishing.

Title: Hart's War
Description: A law student becomes a lieutenant during World War II, is captured and asked to defend a black prisoner of war falsely accused of murder.

Title: Son of the Mask
Description: Tim Avery, an aspiring cartoonist, finds himself in a predicament when his dog stumbles upon the mask of Loki. Then after conceiving an infant son "born of the mask", he discovers just how looney child raising can be.

Title: Shine
Description: Pianist David Helfgott, driven by his father and teachers, has a breakdown. Years later he returns to the piano, to popular if not critical acclaim.

Title: Rocketeer
Description: A young pilot stumbles onto a prototype jetpack that allows him to become a high flying masked hero.

Title: Take Me Home Tonight
Description: Four years after graduation, an awkward high school genius uses his sister's boyfriend's Labor Day party as the perfect opportunity to make his move on his high school crush.

Title: Secondhand Lions
Description: A coming-of-age story about a shy, young boy sent by his irresponsible mother to spend the summer with his wealthy, eccentric uncles in Texas.

Title: Koroshiya 1
Description: As sadomasochistic yakuza enforcer Kakihara searches for his missing boss he comes across Ichi, a repressed and psychotic killer who may be able to inflict levels of pain that Kakihara has only dreamed of.

Title: Cassandra's Dream
Description: The tale of two brothers with serious financial woes. When a third party proposes they turn to crime, things go badly and the two become enemies.

Title: Alfie
Description: A cockney womanizer learns the hard way about the dangers of his actions.

Title: Macbeth
Description: Macbeth, the Thane of Glamis, receives a prophecy from a trio of witches that one day he will become King of Scotland. Consumed by ambition and spurred to action by his wife, Macbeth murders his king and takes the throne for himself.

Title: La pianiste
Description: A young man romantically pursues his masochistic piano teacher.

Title: Spy Kids 3: Game Over
Description: Carmen's caught in a virtual reality game designed by the Kids' new nemesis, the Toymaker. It's up to Juni to save his sister, and ultimately the world.

Title: The Dilemma
Description: A man discovers that his best friend's wife is having an affair.

Title: Le Petit Prince
Description: A little girl lives in a very grown-up world with her mother, who tries to prepare her for it. Her neighbor, the Aviator, introduces the girl to an extraordinary world where anything is possible, the world of the Little Prince.

Title: Pete's Dragon
Description: The adventures of an orphaned boy named Pete and his best friend Elliot, who just so happens to be a dragon.

Title: Keeping the Faith
Description: Two friends, a priest and a rabbi, fall in love with the same woman they knew in their youth, but the religious position of both men denies them romance.

Title: Beavis and Butt-Head Do America
Description: The dim-witted teen duo of Beavis and Butt-Head travel across America in search of their stolen television set.

Title: Blackhat
Description: A furloughed convict and his American and Chinese partners hunt a high-level cybercrime network from Chicago to Los Angeles to Hong Kong to Jakarta.

Title: Ghosts of Mars
Description: In 2176, a Martian police unit is sent to pick up a highly dangerous criminal at a remote mining post. Upon arrival, the cops find that the post has become a charnel house.

Title: The American President
Description: Comedy-drama about a widowed U.S. President and a lobbyist who fall in love. It's all above-board, but "politics is perception", and sparks fly anyway.

Title: Open Water
Description: Based on the true story of two scuba divers accidentally stranded in shark infested waters after their tour boat has left.

Title: True Story
Description: When disgraced New York Times reporter Michael Finkel meets accused killer Christian Longo - who has taken on Finkel's identity - his investigation morphs into a game of cat-and-mouse.

Title: Great Expectations
Description: Modernization of Charles Dickens classic story finds the hapless Finn as a painter in New York City pursuing his unrequited and haughty childhood love.

Title: Gold
Description: Kenny Wells, a prospector desperate for a lucky break, teams up with a similarly eager geologist and sets off on a journey to find gold in the uncharted jungle of Indonesia.

Title: Magic Mike XXL
Description: Three years after Mike bowed out of the stripper life at the top of his game, he and the remaining Kings of Tampa hit the road to Myrtle Beach to put on one last blow-out performance.

Title: Colossal
Description: Gloria is an out-of-work party girl forced to leave her life in New York City and move back home. When reports surface that a giant creature is destroying Seoul, she gradually comes to the realization that she is somehow connected to this phenomenon.

Title: The Rules of Attraction
Description: The incredibly spoiled and overprivileged students of Camden College are a backdrop for an unusual love triangle between a drug dealer, a virgin and a bisexual classmate.

Title: Walk of Shame
Description: A reporter's dream of becoming a news anchor is compromised after a one-night stand leaves her stranded in downtown L.A. without a phone, car, ID or money - and only 8 hours to make it to the most important job interview of her life.

Title: Miss Sloane
Description: In the high-stakes world of political power-brokers, Elizabeth Sloane is the most sought after and formidable lobbyist in D.C. But when taking on the most powerful opponent of her career, she finds winning may come at too high a price.

Title: The Return of the Living Dead
Description: When two bumbling employees at a medical supply warehouse accidentally release a deadly gas into the air, the vapors cause the dead to rise again as zombies.

Title: Draft Day
Description: At the NFL Draft, General Manager Sonny Weaver has the opportunity to rebuild his team when he trades for the number one pick. He must decide what he's willing to sacrifice on a life-changing day for a few hundred young men with NFL dreams.

Title: Rumor Has It...
Description: Sarah Huttinger is a woman who learns that her family was the inspiration for the book and film "The Graduate" -- and that she just might be the offspring of the well-documented event.

Title: Belleville Rendez-vous
Description: When her grandson is kidnapped during the Tour de France, Madame Souza and her beloved pooch Bruno team up with the Belleville Sisters--an aged song-and-dance team from the days of Fred Astaire--to rescue him.

Title: Crash
Description: After getting into a serious car accident, a TV director discovers an underground sub-culture of scarred, omnisexual car-crash victims who use car accidents and the raw sexual energy they produce to try to rejuvenate his sex life with his wife.

Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles II: The Secret of the Ooze
Description: The Turtles and the Shredder battle once again, this time for the last canister of the ooze that created the Turtles, with which Shredder wants to unleash an army of new mutants.

Title: The Love Guru
Description: Pitka, an American raised outside of his country by gurus, returns to the States in order to break into the self-help business. His first challenge is to settle the romantic troubles and subsequent professional skid of a star hockey player whose wife left him for a rival athlete.

Title: Transsiberian
Description: A Transsiberian train journey from China to Moscow becomes a thrilling chase of deception and murder when an American couple encounters a mysterious pair of fellow travelers.

Title: Kalifornia
Description: A journalist duo go on a tour of serial killer murder sites with two companions, unaware that one of them is a serial killer himself.

Title: Woman in Gold
Description: Maria Altmann, an octogenarian Jewish refugee, takes on the Austrian government to recover artwork she believes rightfully belongs to her family.

Title: Working Girl
Description: When a secretary's idea is stolen by her boss, she seizes an opportunity to steal it back by pretending she has her boss' job.

Title: The Proposition
Description: A lawman apprehends a notorious outlaw and gives him nine days to kill his older brother, or else they'll execute his younger brother.

Title: Joe Dirt
Description: After being abandoned by his parents at the Grand Canyon, Joe Dirt tells the story of his journey to find his parents.

Title: Mousehunt
Description: Two stumblebum inheritors are determined to rid their antique house of a mouse who is equally determined to stay where he is.

Title: Show Me Love
Description: Two teenage girls in small-town Sweden. Elin is beautiful, popular, and bored with life. Agnes is friendless, sad, and secretly in love with Elin.

Title: The Crying Game
Description: A British soldier kidnapped by IRA terrorists soon befriends one of his captors, who then becomes drawn into the soldier's world.

Title: Red Dawn
Description: It is the dawn of World War III. In mid-western America, a group of teenagers band together to defend their town, and their country, from invading Soviet forces.

Title: Ride Along 2
Description: As his wedding day approaches, Ben heads to Miami with his soon-to-be brother-in-law James to bring down a drug dealer who's supplying the dealers of Atlanta with product.

Title: The Adventures of Baron Munchausen
Description: An account of Baron Munchausen's supposed travels and fantastical experiences with his band of misfits.

Title: Bride of Chucky
Description: Chucky, the doll possessed by a serial killer, discovers the perfect mate to kill and revive into the body of another doll.

Title: Planet 51
Description: An alien civilization is invaded by Astronaut Chuck Baker, who believes that the planet was uninhabited. Wanted by the military, Baker must get back to his ship before it goes into orbit without him.

Title: The Unborn
Description: A young woman fights the spirit that is slowly taking possession of her.

Title: The Battle of Algiers
Description: In the 1950s, fear and violence escalate as the people of Algiers fight for independence from the French government.

Title: Coneheads
Description: Aliens with conical crania crash-land on Earth.

Title: Everybody Wants Some!!
Description: In 1980, a group of college baseball players navigate their way through the freedoms and responsibilities of unsupervised adulthood.

Title: The East
Description: An operative for an elite private intelligence firm finds her priorities changing dramatically after she is tasked with infiltrating an anarchist group known for executing covert attacks upon major corporations.

Title: Arbitrage
Description: A troubled hedge fund magnate desperate to complete the sale of his trading empire makes an error that forces him to turn to an unlikely person for help.

Title: Pale Rider
Description: A mysterious preacher protects a humble prospector village from a greedy mining company trying to encroach on their land.
Several women enter a science fiction author's life over the course of a few years, after the author has lost the woman he considers his one true love.

Title: Crna macka, beli macor
Description: Matko is a small time hustler, living by the river Danube with his 17 year old son Zare. After a failed business deal he owes money to the much more successful gangster Dadan. Dadan has a ...                See full summary»

Title: Bound
Description: Corky, a tough female ex con and her lover Violet concoct a scheme to steal millions of stashed mob money and pin the blame on Violet's crooked boyfriend Caesar.

Title: 15 Minutes
Description: A homicide detective and a fire marshal must stop a pair of murderers who commit videotaped crimes to become media darlings.
A joint U.S.-Soviet expedition is sent to Jupiter to learn what happened to the Discovery.

Title: Veronica Mars
Description: Years after walking away from her past as a young private eye, Veronica Mars gets pulled back to her hometown, just in time for her high school reunion, in order to help her old flame Logan Echolls, who's embroiled in a murder mystery.

Title: BlacKkKlansman
Description: Ron Stallworth, an African American police officer from Colorado Springs, CO, successfully manages to infiltrate the local Ku Klux Klan branch with the help of a Jewish surrogate who eventually becomes its leader. Based on actual events.

Title: Logan's Run
Description: An idyllic sci-fi future has one major drawback: life must end at the age of 30.

Title: Dinosaur
Description: An orphaned dinosaur raised by lemurs joins an arduous trek to a sancturary after a meteorite shower destroys his family home.

Title: The Brothers Bloom
Description: The Brothers Bloom are the best con men in the world, swindling millionaires with complex scenarios of lust and intrigue. Now they've decided to take on one last job - showing a beautiful and eccentric heiress the time of her life with a romantic adventure that takes them around the world.

Title: Good Time
Description: After a botched bank robbery lands his younger brother in prison, Connie Nikas embarks on a twisted odyssey through the city's underworld in an increasingly desperate-and dangerous-attempt to get his brother Nick out of jail.

Title: U Turn
Description: A man heading to Vegas to pay off his gambling debt before the Russian mafia kills him is forced to stop in an Arizona town where everything that can go wrong does go wrong.

Title: Boiler Room
Description: A college dropout, attempting to win back his father's high standards he gets a job as a broker for a suburban investment firm, which puts him on the fast track to success, but the job might not be as legitimate as it once appeared to be.

Title: Pee-wee's Big Adventure
Description: When eccentric man-child Pee-Wee Herman gets his beloved bike stolen in broad daylight, he sets out across the U.S. on the adventure of his life.

Title: Executive Decision
Description: When terrorists seize control of an airliner, an intelligence analyst accompanies a commando unit for a midair boarding operation.

Title: You Again
Description: When a young woman realizes her brother is about to marry the girl who bullied her in high school, she sets out to expose the fiancée's true colors.

Title: The Golden Child
Description: A private detective specializing in missing children is charged with the task of finding a special child who dark forces want to eliminate.

Title: Courage Under Fire
Description: A U.S. Army officer, despondent about a deadly mistake he made, investigates a female chopper commander's worthiness for the Medal of Honor.

Title: Police Academy 2: Their First Assignment
Description: When a new gang moves into town it's up to the screwball police team to stop them.

Title: Menace II Society
Description: A young street hustler attempts to escape the rigors and temptations of the ghetto in a quest for a better life.

Title: The 51st State
Description: An American master chemist plans to score big on a once in a lifetime drug deal. All does not go as planned and he is soon entangled in a web of deceit.

Title: Rent
Description: This is the film version of the Pulitzer and Tony Award winning musical about Bohemians in the East Village of New York City struggling with life, love and AIDS, and the impacts they have on America.

Title: I Spy
Description: A professional athlete has to help a U.S. government agent recover a missing jet.

Title: Kinsey
Description: A look at the life of Alfred Kinsey, a pioneer in the area of human sexuality research, whose 1948 publication "Sexual Behavior in the Human Male" was one of the first recorded works that saw science address sexual behavior.

Title: Overboard
Description: A cruel but beautiful heiress mocks and cheats over a hired carpenter. When she gets amnesia after an accident, he decides to introduce her to regular life by convincing her they're husband and wife.

Title: Victor Frankenstein
Description: Told from Igor's perspective, we see the troubled young assistant's dark origins, his redemptive friendship with the young medical student Viktor Von Frankenstein, and become eyewitnesses to the emergence of how Frankenstein became the man - and the legend - we know today.

Title: Bulletproof Monk
Description: Based on the very underground comic book, a Tibetan monk becomes a mentor to a young street kid whom he can teach to protect a scroll.

Title: The Sentinel
Description: A Secret Service agent is framed as the mole in an assassination attempt on the President. He must clear his name and foil another assassination attempt while on the run from a Secret Service Protective Intelligence Division agent.

Title: The Producers
Description: Producers Max Bialystock and Leo Bloom make money by producing a sure-fire flop.

Title: Ice Age: Collision Course
Description: Manny, Diego, and Sid join up with Buck to fend off a meteor strike that would destroy the world.

Title: The Last Exorcism
Description: A troubled evangelical minister agrees to let his last exorcism be filmed by a documentary crew.

Title: Ne le dis  personne
Description: An accidental discovery near a doctor's estate stirs up some painful memories eight years after his wife's hideous murder, and now, things are bound to take a turn for the unexpected. Does the good doctor know more than he's letting on?

Title: Lolita
Description: A man marries his landlady so he can take advantage of her daughter.

Title: The Last Temptation of Christ
Description: The life of Jesus Christ, his journey through life as he faces the struggles all humans do, and his final temptation on the cross.

Title: The Loft
Description: Five married guys conspire to secretly share a penthouse loft in the city--a place where they can carry out hidden affairs and indulge in their deepest fantasies. But the fantasy becomes a nightmare when they discover the dead body of an unknown woman in the loft, and they realize one of the group must be involved.

Title: Don 2
Description: An international gangster turns himself in, then dramatically escapes - only to face treachery and betrayal.

Title: The Back-up Plan
Description: A woman conceives twins through artificial insemination, only to meet the man of her dreams on the very same day.

Title: Everything Must Go
Description: When an alcoholic relapses, causing him to lose his wife and his job, he holds a yard sale on his front lawn in an attempt to start over. A new neighbor might be the key to his return to form.

Title: Grave
Description: An innocent teenager, studying to be a vet, develops a craving for human flesh.

Title: Lakeview Terrace
Description: Based on a true story, a troubled and racist African-American L.A.P.D. Officer will stop at nothing to force out a friendly interracial couple who just moved in next door to him.

Title: Martha Marcy May Marlene
Description: Haunted by painful memories and increasing paranoia, a damaged woman struggles to re-assimilate with her family after fleeing an abusive cult.

Title: Jason X
Description: Jason Voorhees returns with a new look, a new machete, and his same murderous attitude as he is awakened on a spaceship in the 25th century.

Title: Don Juan DeMarco
Description: A psychiatrist must cure a young patient that presents himself as Don Juan, the greatest lover in the world.

Title: American Splendor
Description: An original mix of fiction and reality illuminates the life of comic book hero everyman Harvey Pekar.

Title: Dead Man's Shoes
Description: A disaffected soldier returns to his hometown to get even with the thugs who brutalized his mentally-challenged brother years ago.

Title: Deuce Bigalow: European Gigolo
Description: Deuce is tricked again into man-whoring by T.J., only in Amsterdam while other man-whores are being murdered in his midst.

Title: Absolute Power
Description: A career thief witnesses a horrific crime involving the U.S. President.

Title: Littleman
Description: A wannabe dad mistakes a vertically challenged criminal on the lam as his newly adopted son.

Title: Don't Say a Word
Description: When the daughter of a psychiatrist is kidnapped, he's horrified to discover that the abductors' demand is that he break through to a post traumatic stress disorder suffering young woman who knows a secret...

Title: White Noise
Description: An architect's desire to speak with his wife from beyond the grave becomes an obsession with supernatural repercussions.

Title: Lions for Lambs
Description: Injuries sustained by two Army rangers behind enemy lines in Afghanistan set off a sequence of events involving a congressman, a journalist and a professor.

Title: New Nightmare
Description: A demonic force has chosen Freddy Krueger as its portal to the real world. Can Heather Langenkamp play the part of Nancy one last time and trap the evil trying to enter our world?

Title: Whiskey Tango Foxtrot
Description: A journalist recounts her wartime coverage in Afghanistan.

Title: Nine Queens
Description: Two con artists try to swindle a stamp collector by selling him a sheet of counterfeit rare stamps (the "nine queens").

Title: Rabbit Hole
Description: Life for a happy couple is turned upside down after their young son dies in an accident.

Title: The Benchwarmers
Description: A trio of guys try and make up for missed opportunities in childhood by forming a three-player baseball team to compete against standard children baseball squads.

Title: Duplicity
Description: Two ex-government agents turned rival industrial spies have to be at the top of their game when one of their companies prepares to launch a major product. However, they distract each other in more ways than one.

Title: Invasion of the Body Snatchers
Description: In San Francisco, a group of people discover the human race is being replaced one by one, with clones devoid of emotion.
In 1971, a young and disorientated British soldier is accidentally abandoned by his unit following a riot on the deadly streets of Belfast.

Title: Untraceable
Description: FBI agent Jennifer Marsh is tasked with hunting down a seemingly untraceable serial killer who posts live videos of his victims on the Internet. As time runs out, the cat and mouse chase becomes more personal.

Title: Jin ling shi san chai
Description: An American finds refuge during the 1937 Japanese invasion of Nanking in a church with a group of women. Posing as a priest, he attempts to lead the women to safety.

Title: Revenge of the Nerds
Description: At Adams College, a group of bullied outcasts and misfits resolve to fight back for their peace and self-respect.

Title: Nutty Professor II: The Klumps

The famous 1970s New York City nightclub seen and told through the eyes of a young employee.
